[[File:Kongresi i Lushnjes.jpg|thumb|The building where the Congress was held]]
'''Congress of Lushnjë Museum''' is a museum in [[Lushnjë]], Albania. The [[Congress of Lushnjë]] was held here in 1920. In 1970, the building was turned into a museum devoted to [[patriotism]].<ref name="Ward1983">{{cite book|last=Ward|first=Philip|title=Albania: a travel guide|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JJO4AAAAIAAJ|accessdate=10 July 2012|year=1983|publisher=Oleander Press|isbn=978-0-906672-41-9}}</ref> It contains numerous photographs and original documents related to [[Albania|Albania's]] struggle against [[Fascism]].<ref name="Unesco1984">{{cite book|author=Unesco|title=Museum|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6ZToAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=10 July 2012|year=1984|publisher=UNESCO.|page=54}}</ref> The white building has 5 bays on the middle floor and 2 bays on the top floor.

