[[File:Azulejo Mercado Municipal Funchal.JPG|thumb|A work on ceramic tiles depicting a market scene]] The '''Tile Heritage Foundation''' is an [[archival library]] and resource center dedicated to the preservation of [[ceramic]] surfacing materials in the United States. It is located in [[Healdsburg, California]]. Open to the public by appointment. It was founded in 1987 by Joseph Taylor and Sheila Menzies. The archives catalog information about historic and contemporary tile makers in the United States, and maintains a collection of over 4,000 historic and contemporary tiles, all of them donated. The Foundation is a member supported non-profit organization. Sponsorship, grants, gifts and membership as well as contemporary tile sales support the ongoing work of education, publishing and archiving.<ref name="SF Gate">{{cite web|title=Foundation crafts artisan-tile archive|url=http://www.sfgate.com/homeandgarden/article/Foundation-crafts-artisan-tile-archive-4160036.php|website=SF Gate|accessdate=23 July 2015}} </ref><ref name=TileLetter>{{cite web|title=Tile Heritage Foundation celebrates 25th anniversary|url=http://www.tileletter.com/2012/05/tile-heritage-foundation-celebrates-25th-anniversary/|website=TileLetter|accessdate=23 July 2015}}</ref> They have published works on the history of tile in the US.<ref name=HSP>{{cite web|title=Tile heritage:a review of American tile history|url=http://discover.hsp.org/Record/marc-38914/Details|website=Historical Society of Pennsylvania|accessdate=23 July 2015}}</ref>
